<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="147" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[753,1340,1772,2199]" pageId="21" pageNumber="147">
Sometimes placed in genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1160,1268,1856,1885]" class="Mammalia" family="Felidae" genus="Oncifelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="21" pageNumber="147" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Oncifelis</taxonomicName>
. Molecular and morphological data show that present species and 
<taxonomicName box="[1045,1188,1930,1963]" class="Mammalia" family="Felidae" genus="Leopardus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="21" pageNumber="147" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="geoffroyi">L. geoffroyi</taxonomicName>
are closed related sister taxa. Analyses of mtDNA lineages show that these two species last shared a common ancestor about 2-3 million years ago. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="147" type="multiple">
